HB 166 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Jacob Landry
Abstract: Removes Vermilion Parish as a member of the Acadiana Regional Juvenile
Justice District.
Present law (R.S. 15:1109) provides for the membership of the Acadiana Regional Juvenile
Justice District.
Proposed law amends present law to remove Vermilion Parish as a member. Otherwise
retains present law.
Present law (R.S. 15:1109.1) provides for the membership of the Acadiana Regional
Juvenile Justice District Commission.
Proposed law amends present law to reduce the number of commissioners from 11 to 10 and
removes from the commission a qualified elector who is domiciled and residing within
Vermilion Parish, who is jointly appointed by the chief judge and district attorney for the
15th JDC and the sheriff of Vermilion Parish. Otherwise retains present law.
Effective upon signature of governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
(Amends R.S. 15:1109(A) and 1109.1(A)(intro. para.), (9), and (10); Repeals R.S.
15:1109.1(A)(11))
